quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  109,1,"Say [Prophet], ‘Disbelievers"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,you do not worship what I worship
  109,4,I will never worship what you worship
  109,5,you will never worship what I worship
  109,6,you have your religion and I have mine.’
  110,1,"When God’s help comes and He opens up your way [Prophet]"
  110,2,when you see people embracing God’s faith in crowds
  110,3,"celebrate the praise of your Lord and ask His forgiveness: He is always ready to accept repentance"
  111,1,May the hands of Abu Lahab be ruined! May he be ruined too
  111,2,Neither his wealth nor his gains will help him
  111,3,he will burn in the Flaming Fire––
  111,4,"and so will his wife, the firewood-carrier"
  111,5,with a palm-fibre rope around her neck